1.Text: ...Alpha...Alpha...
(Who's there...? Is someone calling out to me...?)
Mmm...?

Ah, awake at last. I've been trying to wake you up
for ages.
You're—
...Zeta?
(This is...a classroom...)

You were out cold, so I wasn't sure what to do. We're
supposed to talk strategy with Nuru today, right?
Huh? Nuru...?

Yeah, that weird little creature who yaps a lot.
I know it's been a while since you saw him, but don't
tell me you forgot the little guy? I feel kinda bad
for him now.

...Oh yeah, I remember now. I suppose that wasn't
very kind of me.

Eh, I'm sure it's fine. I guess he is kinda
forgettable, anyway.

But it still wouldn't be good to keep him waiting.
Okay, Alpha, let's get moving!
Wait, isn't it time for cla—
Huh? But they let school out early today.
They did? Why?

Seems a group of teachers and students all started
feeling sick, so they ended classes right away.
I mean, just look around. No one's here, right?

...Now that you mention it, you're right.
Everyone's gone...
Alpha, did you seriously sleep through it all?
It...seems I did. Thanks for waking me up.

No sweat, that's what friends are for. And I didn't
want to see you get in trouble, either.

Good point... All the good grades in the world
wouldn't save me from a scolding if I nodded off.

Hmm, that is true. But this kind of thing has been
happening on and off lately, so the school is a bit
on edge. That's probably why they get angry if
people stick around instead of leaving.
...Makes sense.
Yep. So, shall we get a move on?

Yeah. Both Nuru and the school will be upset with
us if we stick around here much longer.

...That's funny. This is where we were supposed to
meet...but I don't see hide nor hair of him.
Yeah... Are we sure he isn't inside a dumpster again?
Heheh... Knowing him, it's certainly possible—
Long time no see, you two!
Ack!

Nuru... Did you really have to jump out and scare
us like that?
Sorry 'bout that. I was just so happy to see ya.

I think it's been around two weeks since that day,
the day we took out the evil spirit. How've you
been?

Hanging in there, I guess, considering there's
some bug going around.

Huh, like a cold or something? Doesn't have anything
to do with evil spirits, though. How about you, Alpha?
...Oh, good enough, I suppose.
Good! Sometimes good enough is best!

Anyway, have you found anything oozing with youthful
delusions...by which I mean Dark Histories? How about
run-ins with evil spirits?

Nope. Everything's been so normal, that one day
seems like a dream. You sure these Dark History
things actually exist?

Yeah, because they give off sinister auras. You guys
would know one if you saw it.

Darkollector isn't picking anything up... But if it
does, I assume that means fighting another evil
spirit?

Pretty much. Young people in the throes of adolescence
have no end of worries. That means Dark Histories will
continue to be created.

You mentioned that possibility of even more massive
evil spirits appearing...so I am a little concerned.

Same here. We were wrecked after fighting that last
one... If anything bigger comes along we might be in
real trouble.

Exactly. I really do think we need to boost our
combat abilities.

And we're also going to need allies to gather the
"Bones" that appear when a Dark History is
destroyed.

Bingo. Like you said before, the first thing we need
is more people.

But the more people we have, the bigger this
operation is gonna get... Won't we also need
some kinda base to act as cover?

That's true... But we can think about a base in due
time.

So recruiting comes first. What about that person
you mentioned before, Nuru?
...I mentioned someone?

You did. Some co-developer of Darkollector or
something. The timing is perfect, so make the intro.
Hmm... Oh, right...
Uh... What's that reaction?

...Oh, it's nothing. I'll reach out to set up a
meeting.

Anyway, now that we got our gameplan decided,
let's call it here for today, huh?

Okay. Well, my house is this way, so I'll see you
guys later!
Yeah, see you tomorrow.
Get home safe!
(See you later, eh...)
Uh, Alpha? Something wrong?
...Huh? Did I seem off?

You were just staring at Zeta, so just thought
I'd ask.

Oh... I was just a little sad she had to go.I'm glad
I'll get to see her again, but I was hoping we
could've hung out just a little longer.

That's what we call having a friend, Alpha. And
someday she'll probably become even more
irreplaceable to you.

Heehee, no need to overstate it. I hope it goes the
same with this person you're going to introduce.
Um, about that...
Again with that reaction...?

I mean, c'mon... I can't go making false promises.
She doesn't strike me as the type to join up so
easily.
Is she really that difficult of a person?
Well, you'll see when you meet her...

(I get what Nuru is saying...but I wonder what
she's really like.)

2.Text: ...Okay, we're here. She's inside this room.

"Photography Club"...? That doesn't sound like it
would have anything to do with the making of
Darkollector.
...And even worse, it's THAT photo club.
You know this club, Zeta?
You'll see for yourself. Anyway, in we go. Excuse us!
Oh, wait—

No one's here, even though the door was unlocked.
Did she go somewhere?
No, she's here. See, over there.
Ugh... Pipe down...
Is that blanket moving...?
Mmf... Who's there?
It's me.
Nuru...

Remember how I said there were some people I wanted
you to meet? Well, I brought them here.
*yawn*... Oh...

Her name's Eta. She's a crazy skilled scientist
who's good at IT or whatever.
...So did you really make Darkollector?

Yeah... But for various reasons...I plan to change
it to "Dark X" soon...

Wow, so there's gonna be an update. Maybe there'll
be some new features?
So...? Why did you want to meet me...?
Wait, you don't know? Nuru, didn't you tell her?

I tried to, but she fell asleep. I did at least
manage to get her to promise, though.

Okay, so we're going to have to start from the
beginning, like who we are and what's happened
so far—

...Um, Eta? Are you awake? I've told you pretty much
everything now, but...
...I'm awake.... I think I get the general idea...

And since I run Darkollector, I'd kinda been keeping
tabs on what you've been up to...
That will make this easy. We want you to join—
No.
...Can you at least let me finish?
Even if I did, my answer would be the same...
*sigh*... I knew it was gonna go this way.

But it's not that you aren't interested, right?
I mean, you DID make Darkollector with Nuru,
after all.

Yes, I made Darkollector... And I am involved in
collecting Bones...

But...all of that is just for my research on the
Dark Histories...

Working with anyone else would just be annoying...
I don't want anyone slowing me down…
But—
Hmm... Welp, guess that's just the way it is.
Zeta?

Hey, we're not trying to force anyone here, so all
we can do is face the facts and head home.

(What's gotten into her? I can't believe she's just
giving up so easily...)
C'mon, Alpha, that means you too.
...O-Okay.
Bye-bye...

...Oh, almost forgot. Totally different topic here,
but—

I heard the Photography Club is in danger of being
shut down.
Urk...
Shut down?

You didn't hear, Alpha? The student council has made
announcements about it plenty of times.
...How do you know that?

Because the Photography Club is famous, why else?
...Oh, but I mean that in a bad way.

There's rumors that the club took apart all the fire
alarms in school, and then to top it off, tried to
build an underground shelter beneath campus.
Crazy stuff like that.

And then there's the fact that you're the only
member. In other words you don't even meet
the minimum number of people to be a club.
No wonder it's on the verge of getting axed.

I mean, from the beginning, you've only been using
this club and room however you want, anyway.

...I haven't done anything wrong. Students have the
right to use school equipment.

It's all the student council president's fault for
being such a stickler about the budget. She's...
just trying to find an excuse to shut the club
down...

(After hearing all that, it sounds like she kind of
had it coming...)

You can talk all the trash you want, but it's true
you're almost done for, right? Word is the student
council is about to get serious about disbanding
your little club.
Grr...

Bad behavior is one thing, but not having enough
members really is bad. That can be used as clear
grounds for disbanding the club. How many people
do you need minimum?
...Four. So three more...

But you can't get those three members on your own,
huh? Otherwise you'd already have them.
...So, how about we recruit some members for you?
...Are you...trying to bargain with me?

You get to keep your club going, and we get more
allies. Doesn't sound like a bad deal to me!
Nngh...
...Got it. So, if you find three people...I'll join you.

Heehee, it's a deal, then. Now, just relax and leave
the rest to us.

Relax...? We still need one more person besides us,
no? What's your plan?

Guess we'll just have to come up with something,
huh.

That's so sloppy... This has a big effect on me,
too, you know. Do you get that?

Alright, alright, that's enough scolding. We need to
find a good candidate for our last memb—

...Hold up a sec. Those footsteps approaching
needlessly fast... Could it be...her?
C'mon out!!! I know you're in there, Zeta!

3.Text: Running from a duel is WEAK! Stand and fight!!!
Ugh... She's so annoying...
Shut up...
Do you know Zeta?

Yeah! I'm Delta! And I got business with that
scaredy cat!
You heard her. So, what'd you do?

Beats me. But hey, you're talking like you've never
met Delta before, but aren't you guys in the same
class?
Huh? Oh, um, that's right.

Well, all good if you don't remember. She's just
gonna come bite you for no reason like she is now.
It's not for no reason!!! Why'd you skip PE?!
Zeta, you can't be cutting classes.
Ahaha... Well, it's not like I can say no to you.

But now I found you, so it's, um...whatever you call
it! Game on!!!
No can do. I'm in the middle of something.
Game on!!!
Shut up... Go outside if you're gonna be so noisy...
It's on!!!
...No one's listening...
Hey, you.
What?! I'm busy! Just stay quiet and keep your nose—
What?
Eep?!

Delta, was it? Would you be interested in joining
the Photography Club?

No, no, no! No way! Absolutely not!!! Let me clue
you in on just who it is we're talking about here,
Alpha!

She's a serious troublemaker who has straight F's in
everything except PE and is always in trouble with
teachers for destroying school property!

I don't see an issue. You, her, and Eta will be like
three toublemaking peas in a pod, no?
Grr! I think I smell an insult!
I'm not a problem child...
Um, from any viewpoint, you're nothing but trouble.
Anyway, I'm 100-percent deadset against it!

But it's not like we have any other candidates,
now do we?

Besides, she's got the physical skills to keep up
with you, right? It'd certainly be reassuring to
have her on our side in a fight.

...*sigh* Fine. Gotta crack a few eggs to make an
omelet, huh.
Hey! Stop saying confusing stuff! It's all nonsense!
I'll explain everything, so just listen quietly.

Ulp... Y-You're kinda scary... O-Okay. I'll keep my
mouth zipped.

—And so, we have to destroy the Dark Histories and
exterminate the evil spirits.
Dark pastries...? Inflate evil spirits...?

...It's no good, Alpha. She didn't understand a
word of it.

I-I did too understand! I'll fight evil spirits!
It sounds fun!
So simple-minded...

Nice to see you reacting so positively. So will you
join us?
No, I won't! Because of Zeta!
O-Oh for the love of...

I'm all for having her on the team, but it seems
like we're at a bit of a deadlock here.
Hey, Delta. You want to have duel with Zeta, right?

Yeah! And when I win, she's gonna give me a fried
noodle roll!
What if it were three fried noodle rolls instead?
Hmm? What do you mean?

You'll get your showdown with Zeta, like you want.
And if you win, Zeta, Eta, and I will buy you three
fried noodle rolls.

But if Zeta wins...then you have to join the
Photography Club.
Three fried noodle rolls! I'm in!!!

Alright, I'll be waiting at the gym! Don't even
think of trying to get outta this!
...And off she goes. What a hothead.
How did I get dragged into this...?

Gotta say, that was a jerk move, Alpha. Way to just
decide everything for yourself.
Oh, is someone not confident in her chances?

Don't be silly. I'll get that bonehead in our club,
you'll see.

4.Text:
Good thing the gymnasium was available. I was almost
sure the Sports Club would be using it.

It seems Delta and Zeta's duels...are known for
being rather violent. They probably ran off so
they don't end up as collateral damage...

They also freed up the space when they saw me...
I'm a bit of a VIP... Eheh.

Not sure whether I'd put that on your own bad rep or
the infamy of the Photography Club... Either way, I
guess being a troublemaker has its perks.
What's that supposed to mean...?

Anyway, let's set that topic aside for now.
It looks like they're about to start.

You fine doing this with basketball? I'm pretty sure
that's what they were doing in PE today.
Anything works! I'm gonna mess you up!

(Basketball... I'm guessing that's some kind of
competitive game? This would be a good time
to look it up on my smartphone...)

Since this is between the two of us, it'll be
one-on-one. First to 10 points wins.
(One-on-one...)

(Interesting. These seem like quite the intricate
rules... The players take turns on offense and
defense, and the first to reach the determined
number of points wins.)
So who's on offense first?
Me, of course!
Okay. Let's get this over with.
Alright then... Gyaaaaagh!!!
...Oof!
She just shook Zeta off?!
Hyaaaaah!!!
Whoa, a slam dunk! She can really jump.

Finely planned strategy might be meaningless in the
face of overwhelming power and speed...
First point! I'm awesome!
Yeah, yeah. My turn now.
Heh-heh! I'm gonna stop you dead in your trac—
Here goes.
Aaaaaah!!!
A shot from that far?!
...And it's good. Threes are worth two points, huh.
Grrr...! Scoring points without moving is cheating!

Aww, is the underdog whining? Basketball isn't all
just muscling your way to the basket, you know.
Grrrr...! Ball! Now!
I'm good...and I'm not gonna lose!
...Honestly, this hasn't gone how I imagined at all.

Delta can only get one point at a time... Meanwhile
Zeta gets two in one go... I assumed the latter
would have the advantage, but now...
Oops.
Another miss! Now I can catch up to you!

Eight to nine... Zeta has the lead, but things
aren't looking good. Her fickle nature is
beginning to show itself...

Yeah, her successful shot rate is clearly dropping.
She did switch to normal shots along the way, but
then went back to threes right away...
Maybe she...just doesn't like to run...?
...That may be true.
GRAAAAAAGH!!!
Whoa...?!
Hmph! Now it's nine to nine!!!
So now we have a tie...

Don't worry. Zeta is next on offense. If she makes
this shot—
Okay... Oops, botched that one.
...She missed...

Yeah! Three fried noodle rolls, coming my way!
This is the last—
Huh?
The bell... School's out for the day.

All students on the premises please leave at once.
Once again, all students on the premises—

Looks like we're out of time. Too bad, guess we're
gonna have to call it here for today...
Hey, are you trying to weasel out of this?!

Not at all. I'm just trying to leave since the
school is closing. You don't want to get in
trouble either, do you?
That's true...but then what about our game?

It's nine to nine, so I s'pose that makes it a draw.
See ya.

Phew... That means I don't have to buy any fried
noodle rolls...!

But we didn't get Delta to join the club...
It would've been very reassuring to have
someone with that kind of physical ability
on our side.
Do you really need me that much?
Y-Yes... We would really welcome your help.
Then I'll join this Photography Club! So be happy!
Huh? Why the sudden change of opinion?

Heheheh, because I'm smart! It's better if I stay
close until we finish our business so she can't get
away!

O-Oh... Well, whatever the reason, I'm glad you're
joining up.

In a club with Delta, huh... Sounds like a real
pain, but I suppose I can put up with it for you.

Well, Eta? Are you fine with the three of us joining
your club?

...Yeah. It's going to get a little...no, a lot
noisier...but I can stomach it if this keeps
the club from getting shut down.

(She's scowling while she says it, but maybe...this
is a step in the right direction?)

5.Text:
Wow! So this is a spirit! It's so fluffy!
Fluffy-wuffy!
Urgh! Argh, ugh!!!

Your name's Nuru? Okay, from now on you're my
sidekick!
S-Somebody help me... Urrrgh...
He's been crushed... Shouldn't we do something?

Eh, I'm sure it's fine. At least this way all her
damage focused on one target. You don't want her
bugging you while you try to study, do you?

Good point... In that case, let's continue. If you
would be so kind, Professor Zeta?

Feels kinda weird having you call me that... All I
did was tell you how to use the camera.

Heehee, oh, what's the harm? Now, come on, hurry up
and teach me about filters.

Alright, alright. So, these two photos were taken in
the same place at the same time, but when you apply
a filter...

Wow... They look completely different. I didn't know
the camera could do that.

There's also a timer function. It's helpful for when
you want to take group photos.
...Why the camera study session?

Well, is this not the Photography Club? I need to
know more about cameras and photos.

That's only the name... All I did was take over a
club with no one in it...

So, yes, we do intend to use this club as a front.
We can't go around fighting evil spirits and
collecting Bones openly, after all.

But that's no reason for us to totally ignore the
club's outward appearance. Causing trouble and a
lack of members weren't the only reason you got
recommended for disbandment, right?
Well...

You haven't been doing any of the activities listed
on the club description. That's why the student
council came after you so strongly... Am I wrong?

That's why we need to make sure to also do things
that fall within the club description. Speaking of,
can I take a photo of you?
...No need for that...
Huh?

You don't have to worry...about me... In return...
you can do whatever you want with the club...
S-Sure...

(She's definitely keeping her distance... Did us
joining the club bother her that much?)
Urgh... Rrrrgh... Hnnf!
Ah! He got away!

*pant, gasp*... You all seem to be having trouble
gelling.
You okay there, Nuru?

I-I'm fine...! More importantly, find some way to
loosen up around each other for the battles ahead!

Since you're all in this together, how about
becoming friends? Go hang out around town
and get to know each other.

Good idea... Let's adjourn the club meeting here for
today and go have some fun like Nuru suggested.

You three go ahead... I want to focus on my
research...

You're coming, too! Sitting too much will rot your
brain!

Funny coming from someone with no brain to speak
of... Agh...don't drag me...

This is one time where that bullheadedness of hers
comes in handy. Shall we be off?
Yes, let's. How about you, Nuru?

I'll hold down the fort. Wouldn't want to intrude on
these precious days of youth.

Precious days of youth...? Well, whatever.
We'll be back later.
Crowds...bother me...
You okay? Make sure you don't get lost.
I'll keep an eye on her.

So, where're we going and what're we doing? An old
standby like karaoke seems good for a time like this.

What do you sing, Alpha? Pop music, like stuff by
Epsilon?

Um... So karaoke is a place where you go to sing
something?
Huh? Um, yeah, basically.

Who are we singing for? And, won't we need to
practice together first?

Ahaha, that's not what karaoke is at all. It's more
like passing the mic around singing in a small room.
And the only audience is us.

O-Oh, right... Sorry, it's just I've never done
karaoke before...

Well, then now you really need to experience it.
Okay, today we're doing karaoke!

Don't just pick for everybody! I wanna go bowling!
Just singing is boring!
It's not boring. You're singing and listening, too.

Well, I don't wanna just sit! Moving around is more
fun!
Those two never change...
...Whew.
Is this all too much for you, Eta?
I wouldn't call it too much, but—
...I don't know.
Huh...?
Hey, Alpha, Eta! C'mon, we're going bowling!

Not so fast. You guys would much rather do karaoke
today, right?
Bowling!!!
Karaoke!!!

Good grief... Fine, we'll do karaoke and then go
bowling. Does that work for you, Eta?
...I guess.

6.Text:
(We took a lot of photos during karaoke and bowling
yesterday. I should organize them a bit...)

(Heehee, Delta moves around too much.
She's always a blur.)

(...Eta was awkward the entire time. I wonder what
she meant when she said "I don't know" earlier.)

(If we keep hanging out like that, maybe she'll
eventually... Huh?)
(It's that guy I bumped into before...)
...Hello.
Hm? Oh, hi there, Alpha.
What were you looking at? Something interesting?
Oh, nothing that concerns you. More importantly—
—Is your recruitment drive going well?
...How do you know about that?
I dunno, I can't quite say either.
Don't play dumb with me. Just who are you?

Good question... But really, I think there's
something else you should be worried
about now.

Like...whether relationships built solely on
give-and-take can really be called true
friendships.
Huh? But...
(Could he be talking about us...?)

(Don't just be numbers to fill out the club roster,
make friends with Eta in the real meaning of the
word... Is that what he's trying to say?)
Hey, wait!
...He's gone. *sigh* What was that all about?
...So you two were already here. And Nuru as well.
Heheh, I got here first! You guys were too slow!

I don't remember this being a race, do you? Ugh,
this is what happens when you have dumb-dumb
around who makes everything a competition.
Hey! Did you just call me dumb?!
That's enough. By the way...Eta hasn't arrived yet?

Nope, no sign of her so far. Maybe she felt like
heading straight home today.

If she went home, she went home. But I wanna go bust
some evil spirits!

Hey, it's not like evil spirits just pop up anywhere.
Besides, nothing's showing up on Darkollector.

Grr... That's not what you guys promised! You said
we'd be fighting evil spirits!

Okay, simmer down. We're going to have to fight
eventually, so let's just be patient.

Now then, what say we go collect some Bones? Or
would you rather do Photography Club stuff today?

Before we do anything, can I have a moment? There's
something I want to discuss with you all.
...Discuss?

Now, let's begin this impromptu meeting. The topic is
"How to make friends with Eta."
Why do we have to be friends with her?

Well, if we're going to be working together, it makes
things more difficult with this disconnect we've got
going on with her now.

Correct. I feel that we haven't befriended her in
the truest sense of the word yet...

I say we fight with her! Then we'll know without
doing all this annoying stuff!
Motion rejected.
Awww!

...I guess what it comes down to is that we're
just guests to her.
What do you mean?

So for Eta, this is probably both a club and an
important place she can call her own.

We may now all be in the club with her, but all
we're really doing is sharing the same space.
Like she hasn't really accepted us, I guess.
And so we're "guests"...

If only we could find some way to show her that
we're her friends...
Hmm?
What's wrong?
...I sense something bad.
I'm not seeing any notifications on Darkollector.

No, but I definitely sense it. I think...it's coming
from inside school grounds.

Alright, here we go! It's gotta be an evil spirit!
Show me where it is, now!!!
I'm sensing it from...this way! Follow me!
This is the spot. Any word from Eta?

Nope. Not getting anything from Darkollector either,
so I'm not sure what's up...
Over there, everybody!
Wha?! Is that an evil spirit?!
Wait, who is that fighting there—
Eta?! What're you doing here...?

She invented a device for switching channels...
That's how she got here without my power.
No fair! You can't hog the prey all for yourself!

...Why are you here? I thought I turned off
notifications...

...So it was our admin overlord who kept
Darkollector from working, huh?

Why did you come out here on your own? It's too
dangerous.
...This is what I've been doing all along.
Then at least let us join you in the fight.
...Why?
We don't want to be just guests to you. We...
...want to be your friends!!!

Yeah. Two is better than one, and three is better
than two, right? No need to count Delta.
What?! I wanna bash that evil spirit, too!!!
...I don't understand.

Why do you want to put yourselves in danger...
Why go to this trouble to join me...?
I...can't understand any of it...
Eta...

But...I can't simply ignore these questions...
It wouldn't feel right to leave them...unanswered...

Help me, if that's what you want to do... I need to
understand why you're going to such lengths to be
involved...
...Okay! Of course we will!
Let's do this!!!
Wait. First we need to "awaken" you, Delta.
Awaken?

All you gotta do is say the words you hear in your
head. Can you do the honors, Nuru?
Oh, right, that. Abracadabra, hocus...pocus!
...Huh?
Whoa! My hands are really cool!

Those're "Vier the Claws of Light."
Alright then, good luck out there!
...Wait, you can shorten the process?

Well, time is of the essence here. C'mon, you guys
should get going too.
Talk about rushed...
Time to try out this weapon!

You're strong, but your movements are too simple.
I'll support you...by distracting the enemy.
We need to get in on the fun too.
Yeah, let's show them what we're made of.

7.Text: Good work, gang! This Bone is a real big find too.
Are you hurt, Zeta?

I'm okay. I don't feel as worn out as last time.
I think you should be seeing to her, honestly.
Ungh... I can...still...fight...
Don't overdo it. You're about to pass out.
No, I'm not...! Zeta's...more tired...than me...!

Even that's a competition for you, huh... All of us
were exhausted after our first time.
...This Bone... Hmm...
Oh yeah, are you okay, Eta? You look kinda sleepy...

I'm always sleepy... More importantly...I think...
we may have trouble...
What do you mean?

Evil spirits...have never appeared...this frequently
before... It's possible...something unusual is
happening...
